Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%grams} into thirds. Thinly slice the @red chilli{1}(thinly sliced).

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%grams} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Pour the boiled water into a #medium saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring to a boil.

Add the @egg noodle nest{125%grams} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%grams}(diced), @sliced mushrooms{180%grams} and broccoli to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and the @coleslaw mix{120%grams}. Fry for ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Stir the @hoisin sauce{60%grams}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, @sesame oil{20%ml}, @rice vinegar{15%ml}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts) into the #frying pan{}.

Bring the sauce to the boil, then simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Toss the cooked noodles into the sauce until coated and piping hot, ~{1%minute}.

Taste the sauce and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of @water{} if the sauce is a little too thick.

Share the chicken noodles between your #bowls{}.

Scatter over the sliced chilli (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and peanuts to finish.

Enjoy!